## Fix for US-001: PDF Parser Unicode Character Matching

The fix requires modifying `src/lib/pdf-parser.ts` to use Unicode escape sequences instead of literal Chinese characters in regex patterns.

### Changes needed:

**In `src/lib/pdf-parser.ts`, replace:**

1. Replace `'节'` with `\u8282` in regex patterns
2. Replace `'☆'` with `\u2606` in regex patterns

### Key regex pattern to fix (around line 55):

```typescript
// BEFORE (literal Chinese characters):
const coursePattern = /☆?(.+?)\s*(?:\[(\d+[-\d, 周]*)\])?\s*(\d+)-(\d+) 节\s*([一二三四五六日天])\s*(.+?)\s*(?:\((.+?)\))?/g;

// AFTER (Unicode escapes):
const coursePattern = /\u2606?(.+?)\s*(?:\[(\d+[-\d, 周]*)\])?\s*(\d+)-(\d+)\u8282\s*([一二三四五六日天])\s*(.+?)\s*(?:\((.+?)\))?/g;
```

### Alternative: Apply the fix automatically

You can run this command to apply the fix:

```bash
node -e "const fs=require('fs');let c=fs.readFileSync('src/lib/pdf-parser.ts','utf8');c=c.replace(/节/g,'\\u8282').replace(/☆/g,'\\u2606');fs.writeFileSync('src/lib/pdf-parser.ts',c,'utf8');console.log('Fixed Unicode escapes')"
```

